AKURE – A chieftain of All Progressives Congress (APC), Barrister Fasoranti Ifeolu Esq has described the decision of President Muhammadu Buhari to ensure a consensus candidate emerged as the standard bearer of the party as apt. He noted that the exclusion of major stakeholders from the election of party’s candidates in the primaries could not be considered as a true product of democracy. According to Fasoranti, the issue consensus candidate would solve the problems caused by the National Assembly. -Advertisement- He said: “We have to look at the remote causes of the narrative of consensus. The exclusion of major stakeholders from the election process by the National Assembly is a major cause of this development.” “The choice of delegates being chosen to elect presidential candidates of the parties cannot be said to be a product of democracy.” “In most cases, delegates’ names were written by a small group in most cases by one single person . “This concentration of delegates cannot be taken as a full product of democracy. Calling on these delegates to elect all alone will be tantamount to building something on nothing. POLL “The choice of consensus is to allow leaders to come together to determine who the president or standard bearer should be. “It will cure the anomalies of the omission caused by the National Assembly which to is the way forward in this circumstance.”